<font color="#FF0000">THE WALL</font><br>
<tt>Mon May 26  5:07:49 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I havent visited the wall yet. Oh, i've had the opportunity, and of course the drive from Pennsylvania isnt far. Yet I cant go.  My wife gave me this wonderful print of the wall, you know it; everybody does. It stayed the two days i cried since coming home from Nam; in my office. I asked her to  remove it. I dont know if its the guilt that I didnt die; the shame that i suffered when i got home and went to Rutgers as a secret vet; or my own personal humiliation for not speaking up for my fallen brothers and sisters that has kept me from it. But this is a start......
<p><code>-- db@ncentral.com  (joe buckley) </code><p>


